import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='date')
    data = data.groupby(['year'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend of unemployment rate across all industries from 2000 to 2010?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'series'])['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    max_rate = data.groupby('year')['rate'].max().reset_index()
    data = pd.merge(data, max_rate, on=['year', 'rate'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    sns.set_style("whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x='year', y='rate', hue='series', data=data)
    for i, rate in enumerate(data['rate']):
        chart.text(i, rate, f'{rate:.2f}', ha='center')
    plt.axhline(y=data['rate'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max rate: {data['rate'].max():.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='rate', hue='year', multiple='stack', element='step', kde=True)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unemployment rate across all industries in a given year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
